To evaluate this limit, we notice that:

\begin{align*}
\lim_{x \to \infty}e^{-x} = 0.
\end{align*} So we can rewrite $C$, letting the
variable $z = e^{-x}$.

\begin{align*}
C = \lim_{x \to \infty}\frac{\sin(e^{-x})}{e^{-x}} &= \lim_{z \to 0}\frac{\sin(z)}{z} = 1.
\end{align*} Therefore, our final answer is

\begin{align*}
{\color{blue}C = 1}
\end{align*}

